t, then lex smallest mask) for each pivotXorEffect.\n\n  // Wait, that loses information. We need to consider that different s1effects paired with different\n  // s2effects yield different final pivot popcounts.\n\n  // The correct MITM approach:\n  // We want to minimize: freeCount1 + freeCount2 + pivotPopcount\n  // where pivotPopcount = popcount(basePivot XOR s1effect XOR s2effect)\n  // = popcount of the final pivot state after both halves applied.\n\n  // This three-way optimization doesn't split cleanly.\n\n  // Practical approach: just iterate. If freeVars <= 25, brute force is ~33M, doable in a few seconds.\n  // For freeVars > 25, we need MITM. But in practice with 40 lights and 40 buttons, this is rare.\n\n  // Let's do a hybrid: if freeVars <= 25, brute force. Otherwise, MITM with heuristic.\n\n  // Actually let me just do brute force up to 25 free vars. Beyond that is extremely unlikely\n  // with the constraints (40 lights, 40 buttons).\n\n  if (numFree <= 25) {\n    // Brute force with pruning\n    let bestSolution: number[] | null = null;\n    let bestCount = cols + 1;\n\n    for (let mask = 0; mask < (1 << numFree); mask++) {\n      const freeCount = popcount(BigInt(mask));\n      if (freeCount >= bestCount) continue;\n\n      let pivotState = basePivot;\n      for (let i = 0; i < numFree; i++) {\n        if (mask & (1 << i)) {\n          pivotState ^= freeEffect[i];\n        }\n      }\n\n      const pivotCount = popcount(pivotState);\n      const totalCount = freeCount + pivotCount;\n\n      if (totalCount < bestCount) {\n        bestCount = totalCount;\n        const { solution } = buildSolution(mask);\n        bestSolution = solution;\n      } else if (totalCount === bestCount) {\n        const { solution } = buildSolution(mask);\n        const currentIndices = indicesToArray(solution);\n        const bestIndices = indicesToArray(bestSolution!);\n        if (compareLex(currentIndices, bestIndices) < 0) {\n          bestSolution = solution;\n     